end!</p> <p>Children are invited to practice reading to gentle, trained assistance dogs who love books! The main objective of this program is to provide a relaxed and “dog-friendly” atmosphere, which allows students to practice the skill of reading. By sitting down next to a dog and reading to the dog, all threats of being judged are put aside: the child relaxes, pats the attentive dog, and focuses on the reading. This program occurs on the 1st Saturday of each month.</p> <p><strong>Please do not bring your own personal dogs, pets, or service animals.</strong><br></p> <p>Free. No registration required.</p><p></p><hr><strong></strong>This program is presented by ","activity_type":["indoor","educational"],"age_buckets":["0-2","3-5","6-8","9-12"],"min_price":0,"max_price":0,"location_address":"CA","location_lat":37.3378638,"location_lon":-121.8310846,"location_environment":"outdoor","accessibility_wheelchair":true,"accessibility_stroller":true,"facilities_restrooms":true,"facilities_changingtable":null,"schedule_openinghours":null,"duration_minutes":60,"imageurlthumb":"https://sjpl.bibliocommons.com/events/uploads/images/full/3e377dd30e881a315a924b4ecd43e9e1/ReadingtoDogs.jpg","urlmoreinfo":"https://sjpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69e2679966c3387a9d071667","trail_lengthkm":null,"trail_durationminutes":null,"trail_routetype":null,"event_starttime":"2026-05-02T20:00:00Z","event_endtime":"2026-05-02T21:00:00Z","ticket_url":"https://sjpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69e2679966c3387a9d071667","organizer":"san_jose_public_library","foodvenue_kidmenu":null,"foodvenue_kidcorner":null,"foodvenue_kidamenities":null,"schema_version":"v3.2-scrape","source":"san_jose_public_library","json":{"id":"scrape-san_jose_public_library-69e2679966c3387a9d071667","name":"Reading to Furry Friends","description":"<p>Tell a story to a Furry Friend!</p> <p>Children are invited to practice reading to gentle, trained assistance dogs who love books! The main objective of this program is to provide a